  "text": "neurodegeneration | glial response W idespread axonal degeneration and synapse loss occurs during neurodegenerative disease and after neural trauma. These degradative events result in disruption of neural circuit connectivity and ultimately functional impairment of the nervous system. Identifying molecular cascades that actively promote axonal self-destruction is a key goal. However, despite decades of work, remarkably little is known about the molecular pathways that drive the degeneration of neurites or synapses in any context [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
